'''Callan Rennie Elliot''' (born 7 July 1999) is a New Zealand professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|right back]] for [[A-League Men|A-League]] club [[Auckland FC]] and the [[New Zealand men's national football team|New Zealand national team]].

==Club career==
Born in Scotland and emigrating to New Zealand as a young child, Elliot was educated at [[Nelson College]] and [[Rathkeale College]].<ref name="Niche Cache"/><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/nelson-mail/sport/73136629/paul-ifill-takes-former-nelson-falcons-midfielder-callan-elliot-under-his-wing |title=Paul Ifill takes former Nelson Falcons midfielder Callan Elliot under his wing |first=Phillip |last=Rollo |date=19 October 2015 |work=Nelson Mail |access-date=3 August 2021}}</ref> He began his career with hometown club [[Tasman United]] under the mentorship of teammate [[Paul Ifill]], making his senior debut as a substitute against [[New Zealand Football Championship]] leaders [[Auckland City FC|Auckland City]] on 15 January 2017.<ref name="Niche Cache">{{cite web|url=http://theniche-cache.com/football/2018/10/16/the-welly-nix-sign-callan-elliot-and-mandi-and-were-almost-there|title=The Welly Nix Sign Callan Elliot and Mandi and We're Almost There|website=The Niche Cache |date=16 October 2018 }}</ref> Elliot became a regular starter in the [[2017–18 New Zealand Football Championship|2017–18 season]], where his appearances caught the attention of [[A-League]] side [[Wellington Phoenix FC|Wellington Phoenix]].

===Wellington Phoenix===
Elliot signed a professional contract with Wellington Phoenix at the beginning of the following season, and made his debut as a substitute in an 8–2 win over [[Central Coast Mariners FC|Central Coast Mariners]] on 10 March 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/sport/football/a-league/107853574/wellington-phoenix-sign-nelson-teenager-callan-elliot|title=Wellington Phoenix sign Nelson teenager Callan Elliot|website=Stuff}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nzherald.co.nz/sport/news/article.cfm?c_id=4&objectid=12211153|title=Football: Wellington Phoenix pile eight past Central Coast Mariners, who sack coach|date=9 March 2019|website=www.nzherald.co.nz|accessdate=28 August 2019}}</ref>

===Xanthi===
In September 2020, Elliot signed a three-year deal with Greek club [[Xanthi F.C.|Xanthi]], coached by Australian [[Tony Popovic]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Rollo|first1=Phillip|title=Wellington Phoenix rising star Callan Elliot to join Greek club Xanthi FC|url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/sport/football/a-league/122874355/wellington-phoenix-rising-star-callan-elliot-to-join-greek-club-xanthi-fc |work=[[Stuff (website)|Stuff]] |date=24 September 2020}}</ref>

===Return to Wellington Phoenix===
In July 2021, it was announced that Elliot would rejoin Wellington Phoenix. After 2 years at the club, it was announced on the clubs Instagram that he would be leaving at the end of the 2022–23 A League season.

===Motherwell===
In January 2024, ten months after his departure from Wellington Phoenix, Elliot joined [[Scottish Premiership]] club [[Motherwell F.C.|Motherwell]] on a short-term deal until the end of the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.motherwellfc.co.uk/2024/01/22/callan-elliot-joins-until-end-of-the-season/|title=Callan Elliot joins until end of the season|website=www.motherwellfc.co.uk|date=22 January 2024|accessdate=22 January 2024}}</ref> On 24 May 2024, Motherwell announced that Elliot had been released by the club at the end of his contract.<ref>{{cite web |title=2023/24 END OF SEASON SQUAD UPDATE |url=https://www.motherwellfc.co.uk/2024/05/24/2023-24-end-of-season-squad-update/ |website=motherwellfc.co.uk |publisher=Motherwell F.C. |access-date=24 May 2024 |date=24 May 2024}}</ref>

===Auckland FC===
On 2 July 2024, [[Auckland FC]] announced the signing of Elliot for their inaugural [[A-League Men]]'s [[2024–25 A-League Men|season]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Three more signings for Auckland FC, with two bringing All Whites experience|url=https://aucklandfc.co.nz/news/three-more-signings-for-auckland-fc-with-two-bringing-all-whites-experience/|website=aucklandfc.co.nz|publisher=Auckland FC|access-date=8 July 2024|date=8 July 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20240702210625/https://aucklandfc.co.nz/news/three-more-signings-for-auckland-fc-with-two-bringing-all-whites-experience/|archive-date=2 July 2024|url-status=live}}</ref> This came after two months of speculation when Scottish newspaper [[Daily Record (Scotland)|Daily Record]] reported that he was expected to leave Motherwell for Auckland FC.<ref>{{cite news|title=Callan Elliot to leave Motherwell as Kiwi's departure causes Stuart Kettlewell a right back headache|url=https://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/football/football-transfer-news/callan-elliot-leave-motherwell-kiwis-32799952|website=Daily Record|date=13 May 2024|access-date=14 July 2024}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last= |date=2024-05-13 |title=All Whites defender to leave Scotland to sign for Auckland FC, report claims |url=https://www.friendsoffootballnz.com/2024/05/14/all-whites-defender-to-leave-scotland-to-sign-for-auckland-fc-report-claims/ |access-date=2026-04-16 |website=Friends of Football |language=en-NZ}}</ref>

Elliot scored his first goal for the club in a 2–2 draw with [[Central Coast Mariners FC|Central Coast Mariners]] at [[Mount Smart Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Rd 23 Match Report: Auckland FC 2–2 Central Coast Mariners |url=https://aucklandfc.co.nz/news/rd-23-match-report-auckland-fc-2-2-central-coast-mariners/ |website=Auckland FC |access-date=22 December 2025}}</ref> Elliot made 20 appearances during the [[2024–25 Auckland FC season|2024–25]] season in Auckland's premiership winning season.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Callan Elliot (Midfielder, Auckland FC) : |url=https://www.ultimatealeague.com/player/?player_id=1178 |access-date=2026-04-16 |website=Ultimate A-League |language=en}}</ref> Elliot was primarily used as a backup option to [[Hiroki Sakai]].

==International career==
===Senior===
Elliot was first called up to the [[New Zealand men's national football team|New Zealand]] squad for friendly matches against [[China national football team|China]] in March 2023.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.1news.co.nz/2023/03/09/elliot-earns-debut-call-up-as-all-whites-squad-named-for-china/|title=Elliot earns debut call-up as All Whites squad named for China|website=[[1News]]|date=9 March 2023|access-date=2 April 2023}}</ref> Elliot made his debut on 23 March 2023 in the first match of the series, a scoreless draw.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/sport/football/nz-teams/131541684/all-whites-hang-on-to-draw-with-china-after-red-card-for-tommy-smith-blots-his-50th-match|title=All Whites hang on to draw with China after red card for Tommy Smith blots his 50th match|website=[[Stuff.co.nz]]|date=23 March 2023|access-date=2 April 2023|first=Andrew|last=Voerman}}</ref>

On 14 May 2026, Elliot was named in the 26-man New Zealand squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=New Zealand Squad Named for FIFA World Cup 2026 |url=https://www.nzfootball.co.nz/nzfootball |access-date=2026-05-17 |website=www.nzfootball.co.nz}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Powell |first=Alex |title=Wood, Smith make history as All Whites name 26-man World Cup squad |url=https://www.nzherald.co.nz/sport/football/football-world-cup/fifa-world-cup-live-updates-all-whites-name-squad-for-2026-tournament/VO65EA66YRHJTDPOMT4V2RYVZ4/ |access-date=2026-05-17 |website=NZ Herald |language=en-NZ}}</ref>

